# Backend JS Standards

## Module System
CommonJS everywhere. No ES modules in backend or functions.
```js
// ✅
const { AppError } = require('../middleware/errorHandler');
module.exports = { getAllHobbies, getHobbyById };

// ❌
import { AppError } from '../middleware/errorHandler';
export default router;
```

## Controller Pattern
Two valid styles in this codebase — pick one per controller, don't mix within a file:

### Style A: Try/catch (hobbiesController)
```js
const getItems = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    // ... logic
    res.json({ success: true, data: items });
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error('Get items error:', error);
    throw new AppError('Failed to fetch items', 500);
  }
};
```

### Style B: asyncHandler wrapper (authController)
```js
const asyncHandler = require('express-async-handler');

const getProfile = asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  // ... logic — errors auto-forwarded to error handler
  return res.status(200).json({ success: true, data: profile });
});
```

## Response Format
Always consistent JSON:
```js
// Success
{ success: true, data: ..., pagination?: { page, limit, total, pages } }

// Error
{ success: false, error: 'Human-readable message' }
```

Status codes: `200` success, `201` created, `400` bad input, `401` no auth, `403` forbidden, `404` not found, `500` server error.

## Error Handling
- `AppError` class for operational errors: `throw new AppError('Not found', 404)`
- Central `errorHandler` middleware catches all — maps Mongoose/JWT/Firebase errors to `AppError`
- Log with Winston `logger.error(...)` before throwing
- Never return raw stack traces in production

## Route Definition
```js
const router = express.Router();
const { authenticate } = require('../middleware/authenticate');
const asyncHandler = require('express-async-handler');
const controller = require('../controllers/hobbiesController');

router.get('/', authenticate, asyncHandler(controller.getAllHobbies));
router.get('/:id', authenticate, asyncHandler(controller.getHobbyById));
```

Place specific routes (`/saved`, `/filters`) before parameterized routes (`/:id`).

## Logging
Winston logger from `utils/logger.js`:
```js
const { logger } = require('../utils/logger');
logger.info('Server started on port 3001');
logger.error('Database query failed:', error);
logger.warn('Firebase not configured');
```

## Cloud Functions (v2)
```js
const { onCall, HttpsError } = require('firebase-functions/v2/https');

exports.myFunction = onCall(
  { secrets: ['GEMINI_API_KEY'] },
  async (request) => {
    if (!request.auth) throw new HttpsError('unauthenticated', 'Must be logged in');
    // Return raw objects — no { success: true } wrapper
    return { result: data };
  }
);
```

Cloud Functions return raw objects, not the `{ success, data }` wrapper used by Express.
